# Power Kick


## Welcome @showdialog

**One of the rings is locked away!**  
This activity will show you how to destroy tiles so you can get every point.

![Using powerful kicks to clear the way](/static/skillmap/sc/sc4.gif "Time to live dangerously!")




## Step 2 - Try It!

**üïπÔ∏è Start by moving your sprite through the level üïπÔ∏è**

---

Can you find the ring that's blocked in?



## Step 3 - When B Pressed

**üí• Nothing a powerful kick can't fix üí•**  
We need to remove some walls and tiles! Let's clear the way when the B button is pressed.

---

‚ñ∫ From ``||controller:Controller||``, drag the ``||controller:on [A] button [pressed]||`` container into an empty area of the workspace.

‚ñ∫ Click the letter ``||controller:A||`` and change it to ``||controller:B||``.


```blocks
controller.B.onEvent(ControllerButtonEvent.Pressed, function () {
    
})
```

## Step 4 - Set the explosive

We're going to use a **Projectile** block to clear tiles when we kick.

---

‚ñ∫ From ``||sprites:Sprites||``, drag ``||variables:set [projectile] to projectile from [mySprite] with vx [50] vy [50]||`` into the empty ``||controller:on [B] button [pressed]||`` container.

‚ñ∫ Change both **vx** (horizontal speed) and **vy** (vertical speed) to **0** so the projectile doesn't move off of your sprite.

üí° Don't set the image yet. We'll handle that in another step.



```blocks
controller.B.onEvent(ControllerButtonEvent.Pressed, function () {
    //@highlight
    projectile = sprites.createProjectileFromSprite(img`
. 
`, mySprite, 0, 0)
    
})
```

## Step 5 - Make it powerful

For the explosive to overlap the blocks around it, it needs to **go through walls**!

---

‚ñ∫ From ``||sprites:Sprites||``, drag ``||sprites:set [mySprite] [auto destroy] <OFF>||`` into **the end** of ``||controller:on [B] button [pressed]||`` container, then toggle **`<OFF>`** to **`<ON>`**.

‚ñ∫ Click ``||variables:mySprite||`` and change it to ``||variables:projectile||``.

‚ñ∫ Click ``||sprites:auto destroy||`` and change it to ``||sprites:ghost through walls||``.


```blocks
controller.B.onEvent(ControllerButtonEvent.Pressed, function () {
let projectile = sprites.createProjectileFromSprite(img`
. 
`, mySprite, 0, 0)
    //@highlight
    projectile.setFlag(SpriteFlag.GhostThroughWalls, true)
    
})
```

## Step 6 - Animate It!

In this step, we'll choose **an animation** for our projectile to make it look like our sprite has a powerful kick!

---

‚ñ∫ Click the **Advanced** category in the toolbar to reveal the ``||animation:Animation||`` category.

‚ñ∫ Drag the large ``||animation:animate [mySprite]||`` block to **the end** of ``||controller:on [B] button [pressed]||``. 

‚ñ∫ Click ``||variables:mySprite||`` and change it to ``||variables:projectile||``.


```blocks
controller.B.onEvent(ControllerButtonEvent.Pressed, function () {
    let projectile = sprites.createProjectileFromSprite(assets.image`blank`, mySprite, 0, 0)
    projectile.setFlag(SpriteFlag.GhostThroughWalls, true)
    //@highlight
    animation.runImageAnimation(
    projectile,
    [img`
. 
`],
    500,
    false
    )
})
```

## Step 7 - Choose the Boom!


‚ñ∫ Inside the large ``||animation:animate [mySprite]||`` block, click the empty grey square and toggle to **My Assets** to choose the **break** animation, then click **Done**.  

‚ñ∫ The **interval** should automatically change to **125** ms, but if it doesn't, you can change it yourself.



```blocks
controller.B.onEvent(ControllerButtonEvent.Pressed, function () {
    let projectile = sprites.createProjectileFromSprite(assets.image`blank`, mySprite, 0, 0)
    projectile.setFlag(SpriteFlag.GhostThroughWalls, true)
    //@highlight
    animation.runImageAnimation(
    projectile,
    assets.animation`break`,
    125,
    false
    )
})
```

**BUT WAIT!** There's no kick!  We'll add to it in the next step.



## Step 8 - Kick It!

In this step, we'll choose **an animation** for our sprite's kick!

---

‚ñ∫ From ``||animation:Animation||``, drag the large ``||animation:animate [mySprite]||`` block to **the end** of ``||controller:on [B] button [pressed]||``. 


‚ñ∫ Inside the large ``||animation:animate [mySprite]||`` block, click the empty grey square and toggle to **My Assets** to choose the **kick** animation for your sprite and click **Done**.  

‚ñ∫ The **interval** should automatically change to **125** ms, but if it doesn't, you can change it yourself.



```blocks
controller.B.onEvent(ControllerButtonEvent.Pressed, function () {
    projectile = sprites.createProjectileFromSprite(assets.image`break`, mySprite, 0, 0)
    projectile.setFlag(SpriteFlag.GhostThroughWalls, true)
    animation.runImageAnimation(
    projectile,
    assets.animation`break`,
    125,
    false
    )
    animation.runImageAnimation(
    mySprite,
    assets.animation`x kick`,
    125,
    false
    )
})
```

## Step 9 - Removing Block Tiles

**üí• Kapow üí•**  
When your **break** animation overlaps a platform tile, we need to remove both the wall and the tile.

---

‚ñ∫ From ``||scene:Scene||``, drag the ``||scene:on [sprite] of kind [Player] overlaps [ ] at [location]||`` container into an empty area of the workspace.

‚ñ∫ Click ``||sprites:Player||`` and change it to ``||sprites:Projectile||``.

‚ñ∫ Click the empty tile box and choose the rocky **boulder** platform tile.


```blocks
scene.onOverlapTile(SpriteKind.Projectile, assets.tile`boulder`, function (sprite, location) {
    
})
```

## Step 10 - Removing Walls

‚ñ∫ From ``||scene:Scene||``, drag ``||scene:set wall <OFF> at tilemap col [0] row [0]||`` into the empty ``||scene:on [sprite] of kind [Projectile] overlaps [skyblock] at [location]||`` container.

‚ñ∫ To remove the wall at the location of overlap, drag the ``||variables:location||`` value block out of the ``||scene:on [sprite] of kind [Projectile] overlaps [skyblock] at [location]||`` title and drop it in to replace ``||scene:tilemap col [0] row [0]||``.

![Editing our platformer](/static/skillmap/sc/projectile-wall-off.gif "Time to live dangerously!")


```blocks
scene.onOverlapTile(SpriteKind.Projectile, assets.tile`boulder`, function (sprite, location) {
    //@highlight
    tiles.setWallAt(location, false)
})
```

---

![Editing our platformer](/static/skillmap/jungle/projectile-wall-off.gif "Time to live dangerously!")


## Step 11 - Removing Tiles

Lastly, we need to remove the tile from the same place that we removed the wall.

---

‚ñ∫ From ``||scene:Scene||``, drag the ``||scene:set [ ] at tilemap col [0] row [0]||`` into **the end** of the ``||scene:on [sprite] of kind [Projectile] overlaps [skyblock] at [location]||`` container.

‚ñ∫ To remove the tile at the location of overlap, drag the ``||variables:location||`` value block out of the ``||scene:on [sprite] of kind [Projectile] overlaps [skyblock] at [location]||`` title and drop it in to replace ``||scene:tilemap col [0] row [0]||``.


```blocks
scene.onOverlapTile(SpriteKind.Projectile, assets.tile`boulder`, function (sprite, location) {
    tiles.setWallAt(location, false)
    //@highlight
    tiles.setTileAt(location, assets.tile`transparency16`)
})
```

```customts
namespace sprites {
    //% block="make $thisSprite=variables_get(mySprite) gravity jump"
    export function gravity_jump (thisSprite: Sprite) {
    if (thisSprite.isHittingTile(CollisionDirection.Bottom)) {
        thisSprite.vy = -200
    }
}
}
```
